jQuery
-----------
jQuery is a javascript library.
It is cross platform.
jQuery means "write less do more".
jQuery simplifies AJAX calls and DOM manipulations.
It is free and open source.

Benefits
--------------
jQuery gives web developers and designers an easy way to create effects with almost no coding.
It is easy to implement.
It simplifies HTML document traversing, event handling and AJAX interactions for web development.
It is used in all over the web.

Software Requirements
------------------------------------
jQuery Library
Notepad or any Editor
Browser

All the modern browsers supports jQuery.

Features in jQuery
-------------------------
jQuery provides selectors to retrieve DOM elements based on different criteria like tagname, id, classname , attributename etc.

Events- jQuery library includes functions which are equivalent to DOM events like click, dblclick, mouseenter, mouseleave, blur, keyup, keydown...

Effects and Animations - We can apply special effects to DOM elements like show or hide, fadein or fadeout, sliding effect, animation ,...

AJAX - jQuery includes AJAX functions to load data from servers without reloading the whole page.


Download jQuery
----------------------------
Download from www.jquery.com
include jQuery library.

in system
use script tag
<script type="text/javascript" src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
OR,
use GoogleCDN
<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.7.1/jquery.min.js"></script>


install jquery
npm install jquery from terminal


jQuery library is a single javascript file containing all the its common DOM, events, effects, Ajax functions.


Calling jQuery library functions

jQuery functions will be used as soon as DOM is ready.
to perform event handling we should call the event inside
(document).ready()


jQuery syntax:
---------------------
A jQuery statement starts with dollar sign ($) and ends with a semi colon (;)
in jQuery dollar sign ($) is just an alias name for jQuery.

<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
//write the code to be executed.
alert("welcome to jquery");
});
</script>

eg:
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
$("p").text("jquery paragraph");
});
</script>

<p>Welcome to paragraph</p>
